com.poesys.accounting.dataloader.oldaccounting

Class Transaction

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.poesys.accounting.dataloader.oldaccounting.AbstractReaderDto
      • com.poesys.accounting.dataloader.oldaccounting.Transaction

  • public class Transaction
extends AbstractReaderDto
    Data transfer object for old-accounting transaction data; includes the items for the transaction, loaded separately; contains a factory method that generates the new-accounting transaction data transfer object corresponding to the old-accounting transaction; fields: transaction id (Integer), description (string enclosed by double quotes with trailing blanks), transaction date (format dd-MON-yy), checked (boolean Y/N)
    Author:
    Robert J. Muller

      • Transaction

        public Transaction(java.lang.Integer year,
                   java.io.BufferedReader reader)
        Create a Transaction object reading from a tab-delimited line. The client is responsible for opening and closing the reader. The client should catch the EndOfStream throwable to determine when reading is complete and to then close the reader.
        Parameters:
        year - the fiscal year being read
        reader - the buffered reader set at the current line to read
